|context=[https://github.com/secureblue/secureblue/blob/c824e7e37b8a09d827458a8dac12df0b96e42f37/POSTINSTALL-README.md#create-a-separate-wheel-account-for-admin-purposes secureblue <code>POSTINSTALL-README.md</code> as of git commit <code>c824e7e37b8a09d827458a8dac12df0b96e42f37</code>]
}}

Implemented differently in Kicksecure. User documentation: [[root]]; [[sysmaint]]. Developer documentation: [[Dev/user-sysmaint-split|user-sysmaint-split]]; [[Dev/Strong_Linux_User_Account_Isolation|Strong Linux User Account Isolation]]

<blockquote>
* Brute force protection by locking user accounts for 24 hours after 50 failed login attempts, hardened password encryption and password quality suggestions
</blockquote>

{{quotation
